API Integration Process

First, I installed Sanity in my project. Then, I defined the schema. After that,
I created the importSanityData.mjs file and added the API key there. I included fields such as product.name, product.description, etc.
in the file. Then, I ran npm run import-data in the terminal to fetch data from Sanity.
Finally, I wrote the query to fetch the data in the frontend and displayed it in the form of card

Adjustments in Schema

I added some additional fields, such as slug for dynamic routing.
Additionally, I made a change to the slogan field where the previous value had "slogan" written.

Migration Steps and Tools Used

I used the API provided by Sir and imported the data into Sanity. Then, by using a GROQ query,
I fetched the data and displayed it on the frontend as product cards.
The tools I used include Readymade UI, ChatGPT, CoPilot, and AI extensions, among others.
